msgid ""
"SYNOPSIS:\n"
"\tAdjusting LFS for TV\n"
"HINT:\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: origin/xawtv.txt:11
msgid ""
"In order to activate the existing support for TV-cards, two different "
"options in the kernel have to be selected."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: origin/xawtv.txt:17
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"Character devices --> I2C Support -->\n"
"\tactivate I2C Support plus\n"
"\tadd at least these two options:\n"
"\tI2C bit-banging,\n"
"\tI2C device-interface\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: origin/xawtv.txt:19
msgid "Multimedia devices --> turn on Video4Linux"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: origin/xawtv.txt:22
msgid "For these modules(compiled in as modules) to be loaded correctly"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: origin/xawtv.txt:25
msgid ""
"cat /usr/src/linux/Documentation/video4linux/bttv/Modules.conf \\ >> "
"/etc/modules.conf"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: origin/xawtv.txt:27
msgid "and edit"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: origin/xawtv.txt:30
msgid "options bttv\tcard=... pll=... radio=...  options tuner\ttype=... debug=1"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: origin/xawtv.txt:33
msgid ""
"according to CARDL�ST in documentation, at the same time we create new "
"devices in /dev with the help of"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: origin/xawtv.txt:37
msgid ""
"cp /usr/src/linux/Documentation/video4linux/bttv/MAKEDEV \\ "
"/dev/MAKEDEV.bttv && cd /dev && chmod +x MAKEDEV.bttv ./MAKEDEV.bttv"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: origin/xawtv.txt:40
msgid "xawtv-3.64 compilation: If you have XFree 4.0.1 or later try :"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: origin/xawtv.txt:42
msgid "./configure --with-xfree-ext --with-xvideo"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: origin/xawtv.txt:44
msgid "If it compiles, you have to add"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: origin/xawtv.txt:46
msgid "Load\t\t\"v4l\""
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: origin/xawtv.txt:52
msgid ""
"in the Modules section of your XF86Config file.  If it runs, it should "
"enable you to view TV in higher resolutions, since X is handling the TV "
"card. Look also in the Readme of bttv, in order to find out about support of "
"drivers for X."
msgstr ""
